Description: Fix gs version detection in perl configuration
 This patch fixes the gs version detection in the latex2html perl configuration
 since gs outputs "gs -h" to stderr.
Author: Giuseppe Ghib√≤ <ghibo@mandrakesoft.com>
Bug: http://www.mail-archive.com/latex2html@tug.org/msg02757.html
Bug-Debian: http://bugs.debian.org/320187

--- latex2html-2008-debian1.orig/config/config.pl
+++ latex2html-2008-debian1/config/config.pl
@@ -1043,7 +1043,7 @@ if($opt{'have_pstoimg'}) {
     my $gs_version;
 
     my $flag = 0;
-    unless(open(GS,"$gs -h |")) {
+    unless(open(GS,"$gs -h 2>&1|")) {
       $opt{'have_pstoimg'} = 0;
       logit("Error: could not execute $gs\n");
       &warn_no_images();

